Paper: hep-th/9204032

Date: 1992-04-13

Title: On the Stability of a Stringy Black Hole

Authors: A. Carlini, F. Fucito and M. Martellini

Comments: 14 pages + 1 figure (not included but available on request)

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B289 (1992) 35-44

We study the stability under perturbations of a charged four dimensionalstringy black hole arising from gauging a previously studied WZW model. We findthat the black hole is stable only in the extremal case $Q=M$.